inlineinherited

If called with true this will add entries into the jacobian to link together degrees of freedom that are found to be related through the geometric search system.

These entries are really only used by the Finite Difference Preconditioner and the constraint system right now.

779 else if (auto * const functor = dynamic_cast<Moose::FunctorBase<RealEigenVector> *>(fe_var))

442{
443 std::set<dof_id_type> & ghosted_elems = _subproblem.ghostedElems();
444
445 DofMap & dof_map = dofMap();
446
447 std::vector<dof_id_type> dof_indices;
448
449 System & sys = system();
450
451 unsigned int sys_num = sys.number();
452
453 unsigned int n_vars = sys.n_vars();
454
455 for (const auto & elem_id : ghosted_elems)
456 {
457 Elem * elem = _mesh.elemPtr(elem_id);
458
459 if (elem->active())
460 {
461 dof_map.dof_indices(elem, dof_indices);
462
463 // Only need to ghost it if it's actually not on this processor
464 for (const auto & dof : dof_indices)
465 if (dof < dof_map.first_dof() || dof >= dof_map.end_dof())
466 send_list.push_back(dof);
467
468 // Now add the DoFs from all of the nodes. This is necessary because of block
469 // restricted variables. A variable might not live _on_ this element but it
470 // might live on nodes connected to this element.
471 for (unsigned int n = 0; n < elem->n_nodes(); n++)
472 {
473 Node * node = elem->node_ptr(n);
474
475 // Have to get each variable's dofs
476 for (unsigned int v = 0; v < n_vars; v++)
477 {
478 const Variable & var = sys.variable(v);
479 unsigned int var_num = var.number();
480 unsigned int n_comp = var.n_components();
481
482 // See if this variable has any dofs at this node
483 if (node->n_dofs(sys_num, var_num) > 0)
484 {
485 // Loop over components of the variable
486 for (unsigned int c = 0; c < n_comp; c++)
487 send_list.push_back(node->dof_number(sys_num, var_num, c));
488 }
489 }
490 }

2199 {
2200 // Add this variable's dof's row to be zeroed
2201 zero_rows.push_back(nfc->variable().nodalDofIndex());
2202 }
2203
2204 std::vector<dof_id_type> secondary_dofs(1, nfc->variable().nodalDofIndex());

2206 // Assume that if the user is overwriting the secondary Jacobian, then they are
2207 // supplying Jacobians that do not correspond to their other physics
2208 // (e.g. Kernels), hence we should not apply a scalingFactor that is normally
2209 // based on the order of their other physics (e.g. Kernels)
2210 Real scaling_factor =
2211 nfc->overwriteSecondaryJacobian() ? 1. : nfc->variable().scalingFactor();
2212

2214 nfc->addJacobian(_fe_problem.assembly(0, number()),
2215 nfc->_Kee,
2216 secondary_dofs,
2217 nfc->_connected_dof_indices,
2218 scaling_factor);
2219
2220 // Cache Ken, Kne, Knn
2221 if (nfc->addCouplingEntriesToJacobian())
2222 {
2223 // Make sure we use a proper scaling factor (e.g. don't use an interior scaling
2224 // factor when we're overwriting secondary stuff)
2225 nfc->addJacobian(_fe_problem.assembly(0, number()),
2226 nfc->_Ken,
2227 secondary_dofs,
2228 nfc->primaryVariable().dofIndicesNeighbor(),
2229 scaling_factor);
2230
2231 // Use _connected_dof_indices to get all the correct columns
2232 nfc->addJacobian(_fe_problem.assembly(0, number()),
2233 nfc->_Kne,
2234 nfc->primaryVariable().dofIndicesNeighbor(),
2235 nfc->_connected_dof_indices,
2236 nfc->variable().scalingFactor());
2237
2238 // We've handled Ken and Kne, finally handle Knn
2239 _fe_problem.cacheJacobianNeighbor(0);

2254 nfc->variable().number(), jvar->number(), this->number()))

2268 secondary_dofs,

2270 scaling_factor);

1410 ec->prepareNeighborShapes(ec->variable().number());
1411
1412 ec->reinit(info);
1413 ec->computeResidual();
1414 _fe_problem.cacheResidual(tid);
1415 _fe_problem.cacheResidualNeighbor(tid);
1416 }
1417 _fe_problem.addCachedResidual(tid);
1418 }
1419 }
1420 }
1421
1422 // go over NodeELemConstraints
1423 std::set<dof_id_type> unique_secondary_node_ids;
1424
1425 constraints_applied = false;
1426 residual_has_inserted_values = false;
1427 for (const auto & secondary_id : _mesh.meshSubdomains())
1428 {
1429 for (const auto & primary_id : _mesh.meshSubdomains())
1430 {
1431 if (_constraints.hasActiveNodeElemConstraints(secondary_id, primary_id, displaced))
1432 {
1433 const auto & constraints =
1434 _constraints.getActiveNodeElemConstraints(secondary_id, primary_id, displaced);
1435
1436 // get unique set of ids of all nodes on current block
1437 unique_secondary_node_ids.clear();
1438 const MeshBase & meshhelper = _mesh.getMesh();
1439 for (const auto & elem : as_range(meshhelper.active_subdomain_elements_begin(secondary_id),
1440 meshhelper.active_subdomain_elements_end(secondary_id)))
1441 {
1442 for (auto & n : elem->node_ref_range())
1443 unique_secondary_node_ids.insert(n.id());
1444 }
1445
1446 for (auto secondary_node_id : unique_secondary_node_ids)
1447 {
1448 Node & secondary_node = _mesh.nodeRef(secondary_node_id);
1449 // check if secondary node is on current processor
1450 if (secondary_node.processor_id() == processor_id())
1451 {
1452 // This reinits the variables that exist on the secondary node
1453 _fe_problem.reinitNodeFace(&secondary_node, secondary_id, 0);
1454
1455 // This will set aside residual and jacobian space for the variables that have dofs
1456 // on the secondary node
1457 _fe_problem.prepareAssembly(0);
1458
1459 for (const auto & nec : constraints)
1460 {
1461 if (nec->shouldApply())
1462 {
1463 constraints_applied = true;
1464 nec->computeResidual();
1465
1466 if (nec->overwriteSecondaryResidual())
1467 {
1468 _fe_problem.setResidual(residual, 0);
1469 residual_has_inserted_values = true;
1470 }
1471 else
1472 _fe_problem.cacheResidual(0);
1473 _fe_problem.cacheResidualNeighbor(0);
1474 }
1475 }
1476 _fe_problem.addCachedResidual(0);
1477 }
1478 }
1479 }
1480 }
1481 }
1482 _communicator.max(constraints_applied);
1483
1484 if (constraints_applied)
1485 {
1486 // If any of the above constraints inserted values in the residual, it needs to be assembled
1487 // before adding the cached residuals below.
1488 _communicator.max(residual_has_inserted_values);
1489 if (residual_has_inserted_values)
1490 residual.close();
1491
1492 _fe_problem.addCachedResidualDirectly(residual, 0);
1493 residual.close();
1494
1495 if (_need_residual_ghosted)
1496 *_residual_ghosted = residual;
1497 }
1498
1499 // We may have additional tagged vectors that also need to be accumulated
1500 _fe_problem.addCachedResidual(0);
1501}

inherited

If called with a single string, it is used as the name of a the top-level decomposition split.

If the array is empty, no decomposition is used. In all other cases an error occurs.

Although a single top-level split is allowed in Problem, treat it as a list of splits for conformity with the Split input syntax.
